:1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-10227/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-10227/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-10227/canvas/1/405c2c65-71c7-4e79-aa0d-adecd96d2327","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2025-08-26T19:31:02.610Z","creator":"Olivia Flores","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>As Barry continues down the jet bridge the picture slows down as if he is entering a dream, and he fades as the focus lingers on the bright light outside the window at the end of the bridge. His journey to Hawaii is an entrance into another state of life for Barry, and the white light embodies this transition.&nbsp;The dark jet bridge also signifies Barry's isolation: he is the only person in the jet bridge despite the numerous people behind him in the corridor that leads to it in the previous shots. He leaves his loneliness behind as he walks towards the light (and the plane who will take him to Lena).</p>"}],"target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-10227/canvas/1#xywh=881,365,285,339"}]}]}]}